JEWELLERY designer Sheila Fleet OBE will lend a helping hand when a well known business opens a new store. Jewellers hope new store will be a gem JEWELLERY designer Sheila Fleet OBE will lend a helping hand when a well known business opens a new store.Ogham Jewellery Unit will open on Wednesday October 22 at Luath Walk, in Ayr.Owner Hazel Freedman who runs the business with son Michael, said: &quot;After opening our first store this unit has lots more room.&quot;Ogham is one of the most ancient scripts in Scotland at more than 1500 years old.Sheila said: &quot;The ancient Celtic people's inspiration for the Ogham language and culture was the trees central to their lives.&quot; 